{
  "stem": "2460.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I even saw blonde gypsies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were with their hair.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And those were taken at night, and they were cremated, 18,000 of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We were told in the morning that the gypsies were taken, and they were killed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they let us out from our barracks, and we went into the gypsy barracks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we saw that they lived differently than we.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had heavy-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you know, the heavy bed covers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were also laying on wooden floors.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they had an enormous amount of mustard everywhere.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Food we couldn't find, very little.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they had mustered everywhere.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Later on I found out that they were given the mustard to-- to find out what kind of effect has mustard on people if they eat a lot of mustard.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This what the Hungarian doctors told me in Mauthausen later on, because I told them that we just grabbed jars of mustard and I was eating.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would eat anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had mustard.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we ate mustard.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Next day, I was selected to go to a work camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, next day, exactly next day that the gypsies were taken, afternoon, we got ordered, Appel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mengele by himself.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably, sure.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably they were taken to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the yellings and the cryings were because they were in-- in Auschwitz for a couple years already, in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they knew what it means when they are to be taken.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure, we even smelled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We smelled.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But to me, we-- we were still believing that it's-- it's not human beings that they are burned.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The chimneys were huge.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And during the day, you saw the heavy smoke.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At night, in the evening, you could have seen fire above the chimney.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
